<br>
At level 52 I have, self buffed, 1030 hps and a 500 point (1 peridot costing) skin.  (No ToV gear, nothing special, just gameload.)<br>
<br>
1530 hps.<br>
<br>
A rogue has, say, 2300 hps?  Sound good?<br>
<br>
My lures are nerfed.  Call them 420/shot.<br>
For me to kill the rogue, standing there not attacking me, that's 6 casts.  (6 x 4.5) + 6(refresh, even with clicking) = 33 seconds of cast time.<br>
<br>
Rogue dual-hitting for 35 damage a round and using dly-24 weapons = 70 damage a round @2.4 seconds per round.  In 33 seconds that's 13.75 rounds.  13 x 70 = 910 damage.<br>
<br>
Note that the above 910 damage is WITHOUT ANY KIND OF BACKSTAB.<br>
<br>
If rogue damage is 60 dps, that's 60 x 33 damage...1980 damage in 33 seconds.<br>
<br>
You don't even have to dispel my skin.  Even if I channel EVERY SINGLE LURE and get full hits on EVERY SINGLE LURE you'll still beat me down before I can get off my 6th Lure.  We all know we don't channel 100% of the time, and we all know that rogue damage EASILY surpasses 60dps.<br>
<br>
Thus the imbalance.<br>
<br>
-Szii Uln'hyrr<br>
<br>
Note:  Putting spells at 100% efficiency would put Lures at around 640 for me.  That'll still take me 4 Lures and approx 20 seconds assuming full damage and no interruptions/100% channeling.  It doesn't vastly unbalance the game, but it does make us a threat.<br>
You can kill us @60 dps in 25 seconds.  @ 80dps it's 19.125 seconds.  Why shouldn't we be able to kill you in the same amount of time?<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
